Able to pay a pension not only the Pension Fund of the Russian Federation, but also non-state pension funds.
NPFs are private companies, Volgogradskaya Pravda.ru reports.
They work as a contribution: you make contributions, the fund invests them and eventually returns money to you with interest.
If you are interested in this method, then first study the information on non-state pension funds on the Bank of Russia website.
All funds operate according to uniform rules established by federal laws.
Pension points can be bought by law.
The number of missing points depends on how many years of experience you do not have enough to accrue a pension.
This method is suitable for those who worked informally.
In addition, you can make a contribution for your relative, for example, for a housewife wife.
A recommendation for those who are thinking about retirement at the beginning of their career.
Increased pension payments are received by civil servants, doctors, teachers, agricultural workers and people who have worked a certain number of years in the Far North.
In order not to deny yourself anything with the onset of retirement age, take care of this in advance.
