Media representatives visited the fourth Chernobyl power unit
A video made in the control room of the fourth power unit at the Chernobyl nuclear power plant appeared on the Internet, the video agency Ruptly was the first to publish it on YouTube.
It is noted that access to the fourth Chernobyl reactor control room was given to a group of 15 media representatives as part of the presentation of the guide to the exclusion zone.
According to the RT Telegram channel, the journalists were there in special protective suits for less than five minutes, since the ruins of the power unit destroyed by the explosion still emit radiation, 40 thousand times higher than normal.
The accident at the Chernobyl nuclear power plant occurred on the night of April 26, 1986.
12 regions in Ukraine and 23% of the territory of Belarus were exposed to radiation pollution.
In Russia, 19 regions were affected.
Recall that in July this year, Ukrainian leader Vladimir Zelensky signed a decree according to which a green corridor appeared in the Chernobyl zone, open for tourists.
Also in the exclusion zone, a ban on shooting was lifted.
Earlier it was reported that the Chernobyl exclusion zone from the Belarusian side was opened for tourists.
The organizers of the excursions emphasized that less radiation can be received in the zone per day than during an airplane flight.
