Trade turnover between Russia and Slovakia may reach $ 6 billion by the end of 2019
With the emerging positive trend, trade between Russia and Slovakia can reach 6 billion rubles by the end of 2019, said Slovak Minister of Economics Peter Giga.
At a meeting of the intergovernmental commission on economic, scientific and technical cooperation between the Russian Federation and Slovakia, the Minister noted an increase in trade between the two countries.
Last year, it amounted to 13 percent, an indicator of 5.5 billion dollars was reached.
In the first half of 2019, states reached $ 3 billion in mutual trade, Gigue said.
According to the head of the Ministry of Industry and Trade Denis Manturov, in order to consolidate this positive trend, it is necessary to increase cooperation in the industrial sector.
Earlier it became known that the parliamentarians of Russia and Slovakia are going to hold joint activities to develop tourism between countries, as well as cooperation in the field of health and education.
