A massive crash on Facebook hit Europe.
Ukraine also got
The Facebook social network in Europe experienced a massive malfunction.
Recall that before this, the social network "fell" on September 23.
As Downdetector network monitoring resource informs, Belgium, the Netherlands, Luxembourg, as well as almost the whole of Great Britain are experiencing the most problems with access to social networks.
Large-scale failures are observed on the border of Romania and Bulgaria, in Hungary, Slovakia, Germany, France, Italy, Spain, Portugal.
Also, Facebook is not available practically throughout Poland, sometimes in Belarus and the Baltic countries.
In Ukraine, judging by the compiled map of failures, Facebook is not available in the Kiev region, and also partially in the Kharkov and Vinnitsa regions.
Note that in early September, Wikipedia users also experienced problems.
Which club will take Pavel Mamaev, released on parole?
Footballer Pavel Mamaev, who was released last week from the colony by parole, will not return to the Krasnodar football club.
The former midfielder of this club in the near future may sign a contract with FC Rostov, the Championship portal reports.
According to the publication, negotiations between representatives of Rostov and Mamaev are now in the final stages.
Presumably, the contract with the 31-year-old footballer will be signed for two years with the possibility of extension for another season.
Sport-Express writes that a day earlier Pavel Mamaev had to undergo a medical examination at Dynamo Moscow, but the check did not take place due to the "uncertain situation in the club."
Krasnodar terminated the contract with Mamaev last week by agreement of the parties.
